problem: Nik has 200 crayons. He wants to separate them into groups of 1148362 and put them into boxes.  Each box weighs 1148362 ounces. Each crayon weighs 1 ounce. If he puts all of his crayons into boxes, what is the total weight, in pounds, of the crayons and the boxes, when there are 16 ounces to a pound?
